{"cells": [{"cell_type": "markdown", "metadata": {}, "source": ["# Retail Insights Chatbot\n", "**By Chandan Kumar | Metro Cash & Carry India Pvt. Ltd.**\n\n---\n\nThis notebook demonstrates building an LLM-powered Retail Insights Chatbot using OpenAI GPT and LangChain to answer natural-language queries over CSV/SQL data."]}, {"cell_type": "markdown", "metadata": {}, "source": ["## Setup & Notes\n- This project uses **OpenAI GPT** models. Set your API key as `OPENAI_API_KEY` environment variable.\n- The Streamlit app `app_retail_chatbot.py` demonstrates a simple UI.\n"]}, {"cell_type": "code", "execution_count": None, "metadata": {}, "outputs": [], "source": ["# Install (run in your environment, not inside notebook execution here)\n# pip install openai langchain pandas streamlit sqlalchemy duckdb\n"]}, {"cell_type": "code", "execution_count": None, "metadata": {}, "outputs": [], "source": ["import pandas as pd\n\n# Load small sample sales data\nsales = pd.read_csv("retail_sales_small.csv", parse_dates=["InvoiceDate"])\nsales.head()"]}, {"cell_type": "markdown", "metadata": {}, "source": ["## Example usage with LangChain (pseudo-code)\nBelow is example code showing how to wire up LangChain + OpenAI to answer user queries by running SQL on an in-memory DuckDB table."]}, {"cell_type": "code", "execution_count": None, "metadata": {}, "outputs": [], "source": ["from langchain import OpenAI\nfrom langchain.chains import SQLDatabaseChain\nfrom langchain.sql_database import SQLDatabase\nimport os\n\n# Make sure OPENAI_API_KEY is set in your environment\n# os.environ["OPENAI_API_KEY"] = "sk-..."\n\n# Create DuckDB from DataFrame\nimport duckdb\ncon = duckdb.connect(database=":memory:")\ncon.register("sales", sales)\n\n# Use LangChain SQLDatabase wrapper (example)\n# db = SQLDatabase(con)\n# llm = OpenAI(model_name="gpt-4o-mini")  # replace with desired model\n# chain = SQLDatabaseChain(llm=llm, database=db, verbose=True)\n\n# Example query: chain.run("What were total sales in July 2024?")\n"]}, {"cell_type": "markdown", "metadata": {}, "source": ["## Streamlit App (app_retail_chatbot.py)\nRun `streamlit run app_retail_chatbot.py` to start the demo. The app sends user prompts to OpenAI and can optionally run SQL queries against the dataset."]}, {"cell_type": "code", "execution_count": None, "metadata": {}, "outputs": [], "source": ["# Display a sample of the data\nsales.sample(5)"]}, {"cell_type": "markdown", "metadata": {}, "source": ["## Security & Cost Notes\n- Use API key management and rate limits in production.\n- GPT calls incur cost; cache frequent queries."]}], "metadata": {"kernelspec": {"display_name": "Python 3", "language": "python", "name": "python3"}, "language_info": {"name": "python", "version": "3.x"}}, "nbformat": 4, "nbformat_minor": 2}